p%3EThe%20development%20has%20been%20humiliating%20for%20Russia%2C%20according%20to%20George%20Barros%2C%20a%20Russia%20analyst%20at%20Washington%20DC-based%20think%20tank%20the%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20Russia's%20response%20only%20compounds%20that%2C%20highlighting%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20longstanding%20issue%20with%20command%20and%20control%20with%20which%20Russia%20has%20struggled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe5e8c0e-cf3f-4940-bc02-91699388dfd3%5C%22%3EBungling%20the%20Kursk%20response%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20late%20response%20to%20Ukraine's%20attack%20was%20to%20put%20the%20FSB%20%E2%80%94%20Russia's%20primary%20security%20and%20intelligence%20agency%20%E2%80%94%20in%20charge%20of%20a%20host%20of%20other%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20indicates%20Russia%20has%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20unorthodox%2C%20untested%20command%20and%20control%20structure%20that's%20going%20to%20be%20responding%20to%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Barros%20said.%20Russia%20has%20for%20a%20long%20time%20had%20issues%20with%20command%20and%20control%2C%20which%20is%20key%20to%20directing%20military%2C%20security%2C%20and%20emergency%20response%20forces%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20back%20view%20of%20a%20figure%20in%20a%20green%20camouflage%20jacket%20and%20helmet%20looking%20at%20a%20damaged%20apartment%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c4a6afb4912df3ae1ce8a2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20local%20volunteer%20looks%20at%20a%20building%20damaged%20by%20Ukrainian%20strikes%20in%20Kursk%20on%20August%2016%2C%202024%2C%20following%20Ukraine's%20offensive%20into%20Russia's%20western%20Kursk%20region.%3Cp%3ETATYANA%20MAKEYEVA%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20even%20in%20its%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20was%20planned%20in%20advance%20and%20where%20its%20military%20forces%20are%20organized%20in%20%26quot%3Ba%20very%20conventional%20and%20orthodox%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Russia's%20command%20and%20control%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bhorrific%20and%20very%20ineffective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20faced%20criticized%20for%20its%20poor%20command%20and%20control%20structures%2C%20which%20often%20see%20it%20refuse%20to%20delegate%20responsibility%20like%20Western%20armies%20do%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20slow%20and%20immobile%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20has%20been%20on%20display%20throughout%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20where%20the%20Russians%20have%20been%20slow%20to%20react%20to%20combat%20developments%20and%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhimars-ukraine-perfect-weapon-exploit-russia-bad-logistics-expert-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrought%20many%20commanders%20close%20to%20the%20fighting%2C%20where%20they%20were%20then%20killed%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarfare%20experts%20have%20repeatedly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Frussias-ill-fated-invasion-ukraine-lessons-modern-warfare%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epointed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20critical%20command%20and%20control%20problems%20as%20to%20why%20Russia's%20ground%20forces%20did%20not%20make%20good%20progress%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-did-russia-invade-ukraine-putin-politics-motive-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eits%20invasion%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%2C%20in%20Kursk%2C%20Barros%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwith%20this%20even%20more%20convoluted%20situation%20that%20they're%20going%20into%2C%20I%20have%20remained%20very%20skeptical%20of%20the%20Russian's%20ability%20to%20effectively%20marshal%20all%20these%20disparate%20forces.%20And%20I%20think%20it%20bodes%20poorly%20for%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20the%20Russian%20response.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERajan%20Menon%2C%20a%20senior%20research%20scholar%20at%20Columbia%20University's%20Saltzman%20Institute%20of%20War%20and%20Peace%20Studies%2C%20said%20Ukraine%20has%20been%20able%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20Russia's%20shortcomings%20by%20fighting%20differently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Russians%20have%20a%20very%20centralized%20conception%20of%20warfare%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Ukrainians%20have%20delegated%20a%20lot%20of%20authority%20to%20local%20commanders%2C%20and%20they%20have%20highly%20mobile%20troops%20operating%20on%20multiple%20fronts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20%26quot%3Bit's%20been%20a%20very%20difficult%20thing%20for%20the%20Russians%20to%20figure%20it%20out%20because%20they%20didn't%20expect%20anything%20like%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20unclear%20how%20this%20complex%20scenario%20will%20end%2C%20Menon%20said%20he%20thinks%20%26quot%3Bthe%20key%20point%20to%20bear%20in%20mind%20is%20the%20very%20fact%20that%20this%20could%20have%20happened%20at%20all.%20This%20is%20astonishing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2295bb003d-9722-4ece-9a06-eb2b5c352eb8%5C%22%3EA%20slow%20and%20complicated%20reaction%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EReports%20have%20suggested%20Russia's%20high%20command%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkursk-ukraine-exploited-russias-dysfunctional-military-command-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eignored%20intelligence%20%3C%2Fa%3Eabout%20a%20Ukrainian%20troop%20buildup.%20Ukrainian%20troops%20said%20they%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-soldier-russia-troops-kursk-kids-mandatory-service-wsj-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eable%20to%20enter%20Kursk%20easily%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20warfare%20experts%20said%20Ukraine%20was%20able%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkursk-ukraine-exploited-russias-dysfunctional-military-command-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20take%20advantage%20of%20dysfunction%20in%20Russian%20military%20leadership%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20still%20from%20a%20video%20shows%20a%20soldier%20on%20the%20ground%20supporting%20another%20soldier%20standing%20on%20a%20ridge%20in%20the%20side%20of%20a%20building%20holding%20a%20Ukrainian%20flag%20in%20the%20air%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d09ce2392a3bda9f232158%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20raises%20a%20Ukrainian%20flag%20in%20the%20village%20of%20Guevo%20in%20Russsia's%20Kursk%20region.%3Cp%3EDonbas_Operativnyi%20via%20Telegram%2FREUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBarros%20noted%20that%20Russia's%20response%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20happen%20right%20away.%20It%20took%20many%20days.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20early%20reaction%20was%20small%20and%20involved%20inexperienced%20troops%2C%20which%20did%20little%20to%20slow%20Ukraine%20down.%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20took%20days%20to%20announce%20a%20military%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMenon%20said%20Putin%20appeared%20to%20have%20been%20%26quot%3Bcaught%20completely%20flatfooted.%26quot%3B%20He%20described%20Russia's%20response%20as%20%26quot%3Bsome%20combination%20of%20arrogance%20and%20incompetence%20rolled%20into%20one.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20eventual%20response%20was%20the%20FSB%20being%20put%20in%20charge%2C%20with%20involvement%20from%20Rosgvardia%20(Russia's%20national%20guard)%2C%20some%20troops%20redeployed%20from%20Ukraine%2C%20conscripts%2C%20and%20special%20forces%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EISW%20said%20in%20an%20update%20on%20August%2020%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-struggling-ukraine-kursk-chaotic-command-isw-military-invasion-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%