where%20my%20son%20was.%20Stevie%20rides%20a%20special%20needs%20bus%20with%20four%20other%20kids%2C%20but%20I%20thought%20the%20school%20might%20have%20mistakenly%20put%20him%20on%20the%20main%20bus.%20So%2C%20my%20older%20son%20and%20I%20walked%20to%20the%20neighborhood%20bus%20stop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2226d6e0f3-9520-4150-b48b-025002703888%5C%22%3EWhen%20the%20school%20said%20Stevie%20had%20been%20absent%2C%20I%20called%20911%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20the%20school%20called%20again%20and%20told%20me%20Stevie%20hadn't%20been%20there%20all%20day.%20I%20went%20into%20a%20total%20panic.%20I%20hung%20up%20and%20called%20911.%20The%20school%20called%20back%20and%20confirmed%20they%20had%20checked%20every%20kindergarten%20and%20special%20ed%20class%20%E2%80%94%20no%20Stevie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStevie's%20AirTag%20had%20been%20at%20school%2C%20but%20terrible%20things%20went%20through%20my%20head.%20I%20worried%20that%20his%20backpack%20had%20somehow%20arrived%2C%20but%20my%20child%20didn't.%20I%20even%20wondered%20if%20I'd%20put%20him%20on%20a%20real%20bus%20that%20morning.%20It%20was%20sheer%20terror.%20The%20911%20operator%20could%20tell.%20She%20stayed%20on%20the%20phone%20with%20me%20until%20an%20officer%20arrived%20at%20my%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22830aa8c9-c4d8-4162-8b47-db18f55a754b%5C%22%3EMy%20husband%20and%20the%20police%20used%20the%20tag%20to%20track%20Stevie%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20officer%20was%20immediately%20interested%20in%20the%20AirTag%20data%2C%20and%20he%20radioed%20the%20tag's%20location%20to%20other%20officers.%20I%20would%20have%20chased%20it%20myself%2C%20but%20he%20had%20told%20me%20not%20to%20leave.%20I%20was%20in%20no%20state%20to%20drive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20Andy%20arrived%20home%20from%20work%20early%2C%20and%20he%20didn't%20even%20have%20time%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20car%20before%20I%20sent%20him%20to%20chase%20the%20AirTag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20I%20was%20worried%20that%20we%20were%20focused%20too%20much%20on%20the%20device.%20The%20AirTag%20wasn't%20actually%20on%20Stevie%2C%20and%20if%20we%20were%20chasing%20a%20backpack%20instead%20of%20a%20boy%2C%20my%20son%20could%20already%20be%20across%20state%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndy%20followed%20the%20AirTag%20location%20and%20found%20a%20bus%20for%20people%20with%20special%20needs.%20He%2C%20along%20with%20two%20police%20officers%2C%20pulled%20up%20to%20the%20bus.%20The%20driver%20told%20Andy%20that%20Stevie%20wasn't%20on%20board.%20Luckily%2C%20Andy%20peeked%20in%20the%20windows%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20son%20is%20right%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2289435b4d-e76e-4023-a5be-4477c319a4f1%5C%22%3EThe%20school%20had%20mistaken%20my%20child%20for%20another%20boy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20relieved%20to%20know%20Stevie%20was%20with%20Andy.%20I%20still%20get%20teary%20thinking%20about%20it.%20They%20got%20home%20at%20about%204%3A45%20p.m.%20%E2%80%94%20the%20whole%20incident%20had%20lasted%20about%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%205%3A30%20p.m.%2C%20I%20heard%20from%20the%20school%20again.%20They%20explained%20that%20when%20Stevie%20got%20off%20the%20bus%2C%20they%20asked%20if%20he%20was%20another%20boy.%20Stevie%20didn't%20answer%2C%20so%20they%20assumed%20he%20was%20that%20other%20boy.%20The%20other%20boy%20was%20marked%20present%20when%20he%20wasn't%20at%20school%2C%20and%20Stevie%20was%20marked%20absent.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStevie%20was%20moved%20to%20a%20different%20school%2C%20and%20for%20now%2C%20Andy%20and%20I%20are%20driving%20Stevie%20to%20and%20from%20kindergarten.%20He's%20having%20a%20difficult%20transition%20to%20kindergarten%2C%20but%20after%20this%20experience%2C%20I%20think%20that's%20understandable.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Stevie%20and%20now%20his%20older%20brother%20have%20AirTags%20in%20their%20backpacks%20for%20peace%20of%20mind.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEditor's%20Note%20%E2%80%94%20DeKalb%20Community%20Unit%20School%20District%20428%20pr